\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/td\u003E\r\n    \u003Ctd class=\u0022activeYear\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Ebegins May \u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/td\u003E\r\n    \u003Ctd class=\u0022activeYear\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eends March \u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/td\u003E\r\n    \u003Ctd\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/span\u003E\u003C\/td\u003E\r\n  \u003C\/tr\u003E\r\n\u003C\/table\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Ch2\u003ETimeline Details\u003C\/h2\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EApril 2017 - September 2017, Clemons Library:\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/strong\u003EConstruction completed on Dathel and John Georges Student Center on 2nd floor.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EJuly\u0026nbsp;2017 - April\u0026nbsp;2018, Ivy Stacks:\u003C\/strong\u003E Expansion underway.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EJuly 2017 - December 2019, Alderman Library: \u003C\/strong\u003EPlanning begins in earnest, turning stakeholder goals into reality. Architect selected in November 2017.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAugust 2017 - July 2018, Alderman Library inventory:\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/strong\u003EInventory Alderman Library to facilitate housing collections during construction.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMay - August 2018, Clemons Library:\u003C\/strong\u003E HVAC upgrade\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMay 2018 - May 2019, Clemons Library:\u003C\/strong\u003E First floor renovation will update infrastructure (restrooms, lighting, electrical capacity, and sprinkler system); provide compact shelving for high-use books that will be shelved in this location during the renovation.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EJune 2018, Ivy Stacks:\u003C\/strong\u003E Facility reopens and begins accepting materials scheduled to remain off-site.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMay 2019 - March 2020, Alderman Library collection move:\u003C\/strong\u003E Simultaneously moving books to Clemons first floor (high use materials) and Ivy Stacks (all other Alderman materials).\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EUpdated: 12\/2017\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Ch2 id=\u0022planning\u0022\u003EProject planning history, logistics, and documentation\u003C\/h2\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EThe renovation of Alderman has been a University goal for more than decade, and in that time various engineering studies, historic structure reports, design documents, and other materials have been produced.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EThese documents were created with public funds and so should be public documents, and they may inform the actual renovation that is now going to take place, but their publication on this site does not constitute an endorsement of any of their particulars.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EAs an approved capital project, the Alderman renovation appears on the UVA Budget Office\u2019s current \u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/www.virginia.edu\/budget\/Cap.html\u0022\u003EUniversity Capital Budget\u003C\/a\u003E page. Look for information on \u0022Alderman Library Renewal\u0022 in the Major Capital Projects Plan and Status Report, under \u0022Capital Budgeting Reports.\u0022\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Ch4\u003EReports, documentation, and commentary\u003C\/h4\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cul\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https:\/\/www.library.virginia.edu\/assets\/renovation-documents\/03-Ivy-Stacks-CPSR-1.pdf\u0022\u003EConstruction Project Status Report: Ivy Stacks Expansion \u003C\/a\u003E (2\/2\/2018)\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https:\/\/www.library.virginia.edu\/assets\/renovation-documents\/171012_UVA-Alderman-Library-Study_compressed.pdf\u0022\u003EVision and Goals for the Alderman Library Renovation Project\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;(brightspot strategy, 2017)\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https:\/\/www.library.virginia.edu\/assets\/renovation-documents\/An-Architectural-Program-for-Alderman-Library.pdf\u0022\u003EAn Architectural Program for Alderman Library\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;(Elizabeth Fowler, 2016).\u0026nbsp;Elizabeth Fowler, a member of the English Department faculty, on the value of Alderman Library to the University community.\r\n\t\u003Cul\u003E\r\n\t\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https:\/\/www.library.virginia.edu\/assets\/renovation-documents\/2017_12-fowlerQuestions.pdf\u0022\u003EQuestions excerpted from December 2017 comments\u003C\/a\u003E\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003C\/ul\u003E\r\n\t\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https:\/\/www.library.virginia.edu\/assets\/renovation-documents\/UVLSPS_FINAL-REPORT-full-spread-20151211.pdf\u0022\u003ELibrary System Planning Study\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;(Cannon Design, 2015-2016)\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n \t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https:\/\/www.library.virginia.edu\/assets\/renovation-documents\/On-the-Prospect-151203.pdf\u0022\u003EOn the Prospect of Removing Books from Alderman Library\u003C\/a\u003E\u00a0(David L. Vander Meulen, 12\/3\/2015)\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/www.officearchitect.virginia.edu\/pdfs\/AldermanHSF.pdf\u0022\u003EHistoric Features Survey\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;(Quinn Evans, 2014-2015)\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/www.officearchitect.virginia.edu\/pdfs\/FinalDEGWReportSept92007.pdf\u0022\u003EPlanning and Assessment study of Alderman\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;(DEGW, 2007)\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https:\/\/www.library.virginia.edu\/assets\/renovation-documents\/MLA-Significance-of-Primary-Records.pdf\u0022\u003EStatement on the Significance of Primary Records\u003C\/a\u003E\u00a0(Modern Language Association, 1995)\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\u003C\/ul\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003ENeeds articulated in the brightspot report above (which seeks to\u0026nbsp;define the goals for a renovated Alderman and the activities it will support) 