 a Library class\u003C\/strong\u003E\u003C\/a\u003E.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Ch3\u003EACRL Framework and Shared Planning Materials\u003C\/h3\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022\u0022 data-align=\u0022right\u0022 data-entity-type=\u0022file\u0022 data-entity-uuid=\u0022c0bd12c6-aac4-4aa6-8c7e-2b972529c986\u0022 src=\u0022\/sites\/default\/files\/inline-images\/Drawing_Studio_Art_Class_SS_12-1.jpg\u0022 \/\u003EThe Association of College \u0026amp; Research Libraries (ACRL) has established a\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/www.ala.org\/acrl\/standards\/ilframework\u0022\u003EFramework for information literacy competencies\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;that include six core concepts or \u2018Frames.\u2019\u0026nbsp; The Framework guides and directs our teaching and instructional efforts.\u0026nbsp;ACRL has also created a\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/acrl.libguides.com\/framework\/toolkit\u0022\u003EToolkit\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;and\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/sandbox.acrl.org\/\u0022\u003E\u2018Sandbox\u2019\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;for public use.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe Library has created this editable\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022\/sites\/default\/files\/2017-10\/Lesson_Plan_Template_web.pdf\u0022\u003Elesson plan (PDF)\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/a\u003Ethat will assist you with scaffolding instruction with an eye towards the ACRL Framework.\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/strong\u003E\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/primodb.org\/\u0022\u003EPRIMO (Peer-Reviewed Instructional Materials Online Database)\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;seeks to promote and share\u0026nbsp;\u003Cstrong\u003Epeer-reviewed, librarian-created materials\u003C\/strong\u003E.\u0026nbsp; You can browse or search their database for reusable content.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https:\/\/www.projectcora.org\/\u0022\u003ECORA (Community of Online Research Assignments)\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;is an open access resource for faculty and librarians that offers\u0026nbsp;\u003Cstrong\u003Elesson ideas and plans\u003C\/strong\u003E\u0026nbsp;for Framework-aligned content.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Ch3\u003EInformation Literacy Grants\u003C\/h3\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EFaculty who apply for and receive\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022\/services\/faculty\/information-literacy-grant\/\u0022\u003EInformation Literacy Grants\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;will partner with a librarian to align information literacy skills with course content and pedagogical goals. Students in the course will gain skills and experiences that encourage them to effectively find, evaluate, manage, and use information.\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022\/services\/faculty\/information-literacy-grant\/\u0022\u003ERead more about Information Literacy Grants.\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/a\u003E\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n","format":"basic_html","summary":""}],"field_parent_page":[],"field_path":[{"value":"\/teaching-and-learning"}],"field_serve_via_iframe":[],"field_sidebar":[],"field_subnav":[],"field_upload_a_file":[{"target_id":816,"display":true,"description":"September 2017 T+L newsletter","target_type":"file","target_uuid":"33dda6a3-b3a4-48ca-891b-7a4ff48edc34","url":"https:\/\/drupal.lib.virginia.edu\/sites\/default\/files\/2017-10\/TL-Newsletter-Sept-2017_0.pdf"},{"target_id":817,"display":true,"description":"Lesson plan template, 2017","target_type":"file","target_uuid":"2b1f22b2-bc39-436a-92fe-67145c2626a2","url":"https:\/\/drupal.lib.virginia.edu\/sites\/default\/files\/2017-10\/Lesson_Plan_Template_web.pdf"},{"target_id":818,"display":true,"description":"July 2017 T+L newsletter","target_type":"file","target_uuid":"9e8c54a2-91ff-4fe8-bb02-ae2e4354f2bf","url":"https:\/\/drupal.lib.virginia.edu\/sites\/default\/files\/2017-10\/TL-Newsletter-July-2017.pdf"}]},{"nid":[{"value":858}],"uuid":[{"value":"80fcca2f-960d-4a65-a802-01cec5866ec7"}],"vid":[{"value":3769}],"langcode":[{"value":"en"}],"type":[{"target_id":"page",