embraces the full spectrum of human attributes, perspectives, and cultures.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EThe values of respect, integrity, diversity and inclusion, collaboration, and innovation guide our organization, our behavior, and our interactions.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EWe recognize the dignity of others in both in public and private discourse. We value openness, fairness, and trustworthiness. We encourage and celebrate our differences, seeking out numerous perspectives, including those that challenge the status quo.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EWe are committed to the academic success of our diverse community, and we work hard to promote understanding and inclusion through librarianship.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EWe endorse the recent statements on\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/www.arl.org\/news\/arl-news\/4154#.WLBVFBIrJm9\u0022\u003Einclusion\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;and\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/www.arl.org\/news\/arl-news\/4204-research-libraries-university-presses-oppose-trumps-immigration-order#.WLBVcBIrJm_\u0022\u003Eimmigration\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;by the Association of Research Libraries (ARL), of which we are a member institution, and we adhere to the University of Virginia\u2019s core values identified in its\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/www.virginia.edu\/statementofpurpose\/purpose.html\u0022\u003Emission statement\u003C\/a\u003E:\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cul\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003Eenduring commitment to a vibrant and unique residential learning environment marked by the free and collegial exchange of ideas;\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003Eunwavering support of a collaborative, diverse community bound together by distinctive foundational values of honor, integrity, trust, and respect;\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003Euniversal dedication to excellence and affordable access.\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\u003C\/ul\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThis Library is open to all, and all are welcome here.\u003C\/strong\u003E\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n","format":"basic_html","summary":""}],"field_parent_page":[],"field_path":[{"value":"\/affirmation-of-values"}],"field_serve_via_iframe":[],"field_sidebar":[],"field_subnav":[],"field_upload_a_file":[]},{"nid":[{"value":803}],"uuid":[{"value":"2c39adae-089f-40f3-9235-728b92509d40"}],"vid":[{"value":3914}],"langcode":[{"value":"en"}],"type":[{"target_id":"page","target_type":"node_type","target_uuid":"17745858-15d2-4bcb-bc99-14fe05bb598b"}],"status":[{"value":true}],"title":[{"value":"About UVA Library"}],"uid":[{"target_id":23,"target_type":"user","target_uuid":"65ab37fa-d1ff-480d-ad29-54793bbc7fb0","url":"\/user\/23"}],"created":[{"value":1499107887}],"changed":[{"value":1521479141}],"promote":[{"value":false}],"sticky":[{"value":false}],"revision_timestamp":[{"value":1521479141}],"revision_uid":[{"target_id":12,"target_type":"user","target_uuid":"439d086d-5c77-4435-8ce2-0d00e5f90bed","url":"\/user\/12"}],"revision_log":[],"revision_translation_affected":[{"value":true}],"default_langcode":[{"value":true}],"path":[],"publish_on":[],"unpublish_on":[],"body":[{"value":"\u003Cdiv class=\u0022layout horizontal wrap\u0022\u003E\r\n  \u003Cfigure id=\u0022profileImage\u0022\u003E\r\n    \u003Ciron-image class=\u0022round\u0022 src=\u0022\/files\/2017-05\/jmu2m_0.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C\/iron-image\u003E\r\n    \u003Cfigcaption class=\u0022noBG\u0022\u003EJohn Unsworth, University Librarian and Dean of Libraries\u003C\/figcaption\u003E\r\n  \u003C\/figure\u003E\r\n  \r\n  \u003Cdiv id=\u0022profile\u0022 class=\u0022layout flex\u0022\u003E\r\n    \u003Cp class=\u0022bigFirstLetter\u0022\u003EThe University of Virginia was conceived with a library at its heart, placed in the Rotunda at the head of the Academical Village. The Library\u2019s first collection was selected by Thomas Jefferson and arranged according to a classification scheme he adapted from Francis Bacon\u2019s \u003Cem\u003EThe Advancement of Learning\u003C\/em\u003E. Today, the Library\u2019s original purpose remains unchanged: to provide access to accumulated knowledge, and in so doing, increase it\u2014in short, to advance learning. In pursuit of that goal, we collect, preserve, organize, and share \u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/search.lib.virginia.edu\/\u0022\u003Ematerials of all kinds\u003C\/a\u003E.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n    \u003Cp\u003EThe Library\u0027s staff, services, and resources are here to ensure that the University community has the information it needs for teaching, research, and personal enjoyment and enrichment. We invite you to \u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/static.lib.virginia.edu\/directory\/organization.html\u0022\u003Elearn more about the organization\u003C\/a\u003E that makes up the UVA Library today, and the services we provide.\u003C\/p\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022aboutSig\u0022 data-align=\u0022right\u0022 src=\u0022https:\/\/drupal.lib.virginia.edu\/sites\/default\/files\/2018-02\/JUsig.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022Unsworth signature\u0022 \/\u003E\r\n  \u003C\/div\u003E\r\n\u003C\/div\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022shady layout horizontal wrap center-justified\u0022\u003E\r\n  \u003Cdiv class=\u0022flex-4 layout horizontal wrap center-justified\u0022\u003E\r\n    \u003Cpaper-card id=\u0022learn\u0022 class=\u0022flex\u0022 heading=\u0022More about UVA Libraries\u0022 image=\u0022https:\/\/drupal.lib.virginia.edu\/sites\/default\/files\/2018-02\/LearnAbout.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022exterior of the Harrison-Small Special Collections Library\u0022\u003E\r\n      \u003Cdiv class=\u0022card-content\u0022\u003E\r\n        \u003Ch3\u003EUsing our libraries\u003C\/h3\u003E\r\n        \u003Cul class=\u0022uvalib-card-list\u0022\u003E\r\n          \u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/static.lib.virginia.edu\/directory\/libraries.html\u0022\u003ELibraries \u0026amp; Labs\u003C\/a\u003E\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n          \u003Cli\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https:\/\/www.library.virginia.edu\/policies\/\u0022\u003