"},{"target_id":1080,"display":true,"description":"","target_type":"file","target_uuid":"f05984fa-6268-46a6-8163-63880a6d91fa","url":"https:\/\/drupal.lib.virginia.edu\/sites\/default\/files\/2018-02\/QuickFacts.jpg"}]},{"nid":[{"value":802}],"uuid":[{"value":"9c40cc98-be37-4553-a32f-e92ccb3affde"}],"vid":[{"value":3794}],"langcode":[{"value":"en"}],"type":[{"target_id":"page","target_type":"node_type","target_uuid":"17745858-15d2-4bcb-bc99-14fe05bb598b"}],"status":[{"value":true}],"title":[{"value":"About Available to Order Items"}],"uid":[{"target_id":23,"target_type":"user","target_uuid":"65ab37fa-d1ff-480d-ad29-54793bbc7fb0","url":"\/user\/23"}],"created":[{"value":1499107016}],"changed":[{"value":1520974323}],"promote":[{"value":false}],"sticky":[{"value":false}],"revision_timestamp":[{"value":1520974323}],"revision_uid":[{"target_id":5,"target_type":"user","target_uuid":"72805735-7df1-4da2-94b5-f7a9266fd67e","url":"\/user\/5"}],"revision_log":[],"revision_translation_affected":[],"default_langcode":[{"value":true}],"path":[],"publish_on":[],"unpublish_on":[],"body":[{"value":"\u003Cp\u003EOur Available to Order service enhances\u0026nbsp;the way we currently acquire books for the Library\u2019s permanent collection by inviting\u0026nbsp;you to participate in our collection building. Librarians curate selections\u0026nbsp;of books\u0026nbsp;beyond our usual purchases, which are then made available as Virgo catalog records. Should you choose to order these items, the Library will purchase them to become part of our collection.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EThis service\u0026nbsp;allows you to choose books you need for your research and scholarship from right inside the Library catalog.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Ch3\u003EWhat are Available to Order books?\u003C\/h3\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cul\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECurated lists of English language monographs\u003C\/strong\u003E\u0026nbsp;selected by our Library collection staff that appear in Virgo as \u201cAvailable to Order\u201d items. You may prompt the Library to purchase these items from within Virgo.\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBooks that enhance\u0026nbsp;\u003C\/strong\u003Eour current collection development efforts\u003Cstrong\u003E.\u003C\/strong\u003E\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\u003C\/ul\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Ch3\u003EWhat are the benefits?\u003C\/h3\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cul\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases\u0026nbsp;your access\u003C\/strong\u003E\u0026nbsp;to scholarly materials\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EYou\u003C\/strong\u003E\u0026nbsp;\u003Cstrong\u003Ehelp us build a Library collection\u003C\/strong\u003E\u0026nbsp;that best supports your research and scholarship\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003EWe more\u0026nbsp;\u003Cstrong\u003Edirectly support your research needs\u003C\/strong\u003E\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003EWe can\u0026nbsp;\u003Cstrong\u003Efocus our funding\u003C\/strong\u003E\u0026nbsp;on books you need\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\u003C\/ul\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Ch3\u003EWhat happens when I request an Available to Order book?\u003C\/h3\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EAs soon as we receive your request, we\u2019ll purchase the item. Available to Order books will arrive in about 10 business days. A hold will be placed on the book for you,\u0026nbsp;and you\u2019ll be able to pick it up at a library, or if you\u2019re eligible for\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022https:\/\/www.library.virginia.edu\/services\/ils\/leo\/\u0022\u003ELEO\u003C\/a\u003E delivery, it will be delivered to you.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Ch3\u003ECan I still place an\u0026nbsp;ILL request for a book?\u003C\/h3\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cp\u003EYes! You can always place\u0026nbsp;an\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022\/services\/ils\/\u0022\u003EInterlibrary Loan request\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;\u003Cstrong\u003Efor a book that isn\u2019t in Virgo\u003C\/strong\u003E, or\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022\/askalibrarian\/\u0022\u003EAsk a Librarian\u003C\/a\u003E\u0026nbsp;to learn about other options for obtaining what you need.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Ch3\u003EWho should I contact with questions?\u003C\/h3\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Cul\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003EFor general\u003Cstrong\u003E\u0026nbsp;questions about using this service or obtaining materials\u003C\/strong\u003E\u0026nbsp;contact\u0026nbsp;us via\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022\/askalibrarian\/\u0022\u003EAsk a Librarian\u003C\/a\u003E\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003EFor questions about\u0026nbsp;\u003Cstrong\u003Ehow the Available to Order\u0026nbsp;service is administered\u003C\/strong\u003E, email\u0026nbsp;\u003Ca href=\u0022mailto:lib-collections@virginia.edu?subject=PDA%20Service\u0022\u003EBeth Blanton-Kent\u003C\/a\u003E\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n\u003C\/ul\u003E\r\n","format":"basic_html","summary":""}],"field_parent_page":[],"field_path":[{"value":"\/about-available-to-order-items"}],"field_serve_via_iframe":[{"value":false}],"field_sidebar":[],"field_subnav":[],"field_upload_a_file":[]},{"nid":[{"value":799}],"uuid":[{"value":"b7008a5c-0340-4cd1-aa7e-cb87bb9836fd"}],"vid":[{"value":3754}],"langcode":[{"value":"en"}],"type":[{"target_id":"page","target_type":"node_type","target_uuid":"17745858-15d2-4bcb-bc99-14fe05bb598b"}],"status":[{"value":true}],"title":[{"value":"Off-Grounds Access"}],"uid":[{"target_id":26,"target_type":"user","target_uuid":"507db1cb-861f-490d-a7fe-370e14b1c1e8","url":"\/user\/26"}],"created":[{"value":1498680370}],"changed":[{"value":1520456474}],"promote":[{"value":false}],"sticky":[{"value":false}],"revision_timestamp":[{"value":1520456474}],"revision_uid":[{"target_id":29,"target_type":"user","target_uuid":"6a90bc39-8567-443e-9726-9ea9be8145fa","url":"\/user\/29"}],"revision_log":[],"revision_translation_affected":[{"value":true}],"default_langcode":[{"value":true}],"path":[],"publish_on":[],"unpublish_on":[],"body":[{"value":"    \u003Cp\u003EThe Libraries provide three types of web resources:\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n    \u003Cul\u003E\r\n    \t\u003Cli\u003EE-books, images and other databases created by the Libraries. These are either out of copyright or were created at the University and are generally freely available to all.\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n    \t\u003Cli\u003EE-books, e-journals, and other databases provided via open access.\u0026nbsp; These are generally provided by a publisher or government agency and are freely available to all.\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n    \t\u003Cli\u003EE-books, e-journals, images and other databases that are covered by copyright. The Libraries license their use for the University and the contracts generally restrict use to students, faculty and staff of the University. See \u003Ca href=\u0022\/policies\/access-to-databases\/\u0022\u003Eaccess policy information\u003C\/a\u003E if you\u0027re not sure about your user status.\u003C\/li\u003E\r\n    \u003C\/ul\u003E\r\n    \u003Cp\u003EThese licensed databases can normally be used only from computers on Grounds, but there are workarounds to allow use from home or while traveling.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n    \u003Cdiv class=\u0022layout horizontal center-justified\u0022\u003E\r\n      \u003Cpaper-card id=\u0022EZproxy\u0022 heading=\u0022EZproxy\u0022 elevation=\u00221\u0022 aria-label=\u0022EZproxy\u0022\u003E\r\n        \u003Cdiv class=\u0022card-content\u0022\u003E\r\n          \u003Cp\u003EITS maintains a proxy server (EZproxy) that provides access to selected web resources, including all UVA Library databases. You simply logon via the NetBadge prompt when attempting to access a database that you would link to from the Library\u2019s website.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n          \u003Cp\u003EEZProxy can provide good access to licensed web resources. It simply requires a NetBadge login, and will also work on any platform\/browser, including mobile devices.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n          \u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/www.itc.virginia.edu\/network\/proxy\/\u0022\u003E\u003Cpaper-button raised\u003EGo to EZproxy\u003C\/paper-button\u003E\u003C\/a\u003E\r\n        \u003C\/div\u003E\r\n      \u003C\/paper-card\u003E\r\n      \u003Cpaper-card id=\u0022UVAAnywhere\u0022 heading=\u0022UVA Anywhere\u0022 elevation=\u00221\u0022 aria-label=\u0022UVA Anywhere\u0022\u003E\r\n        \u003Cdiv class=\u0022card-content\u0022\u003E\r\n          \u003Cp\u003EITS provides a \u0022virtual private network\u0022 that puts your computer temporarily on the UVA network. You\u2019ll need to register with ITS to put a certificate on your computer, and then download and install the network software.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n          \u003Cp\u003EUVA Anywhere is available for Windows, Linux, and Macintosh computers. Once configured, UVA Anywhere provides reliable, fast access not only to Library databases, but also to non-web resources such as EndNote and Home Directory. Setup is more complicated than for proxy and requires downloading software. There can be problems with software firewalls and with some Internet service providers, including AOL.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n          \u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/www.itc.virginia.edu\/network\/vpn\/\u0022\u003E\u003Cpaper-button raised\u003EGo to UVA Anywhere\u003C\/paper-button\u003E\u003C\/a\u003E\r\n        \u003C\/div\u003E\r\n      \u003C\/paper-card\u003E\r\n      \u003Cpaper-card id=\u0022UVAAnywhereLite\u0022 heading=\u0022UVA Anywhere-Lite\u0022 elevation=\u00221\u0022 aria-label=\u0022UVA Anywhere-Lite\u0022\u003E\r\n        \u003Cdiv class=\u0022card-content\u0022\u003E\r\n          \u003Cp\u003EUVA Anywhere-Lite WebVPN enables UVA students and employees to access restricted resources such as online library journals and software downloads from off-Grounds using just a web browser. These resources would normally be accessible \u003Cem\u003Eonly\u003C\/em\u003E if your computer is physically located on Grounds and connected to the University network.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n          \u003Cp\u003EUVA Anywhere-Lite is \u003Cem\u003Enot\u003C\/em\u003E a full replacement for the standard UVA Anywhere VPN, which protects \u003Cem\u003Eall\u003C\/em\u003E network traffic, whether or not it\u2019s web-based, between your machine and the UVA network. Install and use the full UVA Anywhere service where possible, and use UVA Anywhere-Lite when you need access only to access web-based resources.\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n          \u003Ca href=\u0022http:\/\/its.virginia.edu\/network\/vpn\/webvpn\/\u0022\u003E\u003Cpaper-button raised\u003EGo to UVA Anywhere-Lite\u003C\/paper-button\u003E\u003C\/a\u003E\r\n        \u003C\/div\u003E\r\n      \u003C\/paper-card\u003E\r\n    \u003C\/div\u003E","format":"full_html","summary":""}],"field_parent_page":[{"target_id":1107,"target_type":"node","target_uuid":"8d40f2c4-6a70-4e17-b1c2-7984b32909ac","url":"\/node\/1107"}],"field_path":[{"value":"\/services\/off-grounds-access\/"}],"field_serve_via_iframe":[{"value":false}],"field_sidebar":[],"field_subnav":[],"field_upload_a_file":[]},{"nid":[{"value":798}],"uuid":[{"value":"14e04122-985d-49ed-b7da-e1ee3d2ea379"}],"vid":[{"value":3564}],"langcode":[{"value":"en"}],"type":[{"target_id":"page","target_type":"node_type","target_uuid":"17745858-15d2-4bcb-bc99-14fe05bb598b"}],"status":[{"value":true}],"title":[{"value":"NetBadge Logout"}],"uid":[{"target_id":26,"target_type":"user","target_uuid":"507db1cb-861f-490d-a7fe-370e14b1c1e8","url":"\/user\/26"}],"created":[{"value":1498680022}],"changed":[{"value":1520028254}],"promote":[{"value":false}],"sticky":[{"value":false}],"revision_timestamp":[{"value":1520028254}],"revision_uid":[{"target_id":12,"target_type":"user","target_uuid":"439d086d-5c77-4435-8ce2-0d00e5f90bed","url":"\/user\/12"}],"revision_log":[],"revision_translation_affected":[{"value":true}],"default_langcode":[{"value":true}],"path":[],"publish_on":[],"unpublish_on":[],"body":[{"value":"\u003Cp\u003EWARNING: Protect your privacy! Prevent unauthorized use!\u003C\/p\u003E\r\n\r\n\u003Col\u003E\r\n\t\u003Cli\u003EExit your browser \u003Cstrong\